sex education can make you a stronger advocate against discrimination when you come up against it because you recognize its weight. &#10;This could work for boys as well with the right teachers and environment. Gandy's belief that boys will always naturally feel like they have to beat out the girls or that they are smarter than girls is a form of sterotyping. It isn't like we are saying that a girl who has never beaten a boy on an algebra test will have a problem with a male supervisor. &#10;Single sex is not for everyone but it is for some of us, especially with the right instruction. &#10;And anything (ANYTHING) that we can do that will lower the oversexualization of today's elementary school population is fantastic. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1024" language="en" documentId="2138" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="panda" date="3/11/09 1:57pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://jezebel.com/5168107/same+sex-education-the-separation-debate?comment=11287890#comments" topic="single-sex-education" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="2138" notes="" title="Same-Sex Education: The Separation Debate"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="439"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="440" end="795"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="796" end="892"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="893" end="1024"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>